{
  "stem": "24111.7",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were four people and [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Elise. ?] And Joschko asked him if it would be possible to unite-- to get us out from there and bring us into the same-- the same group again.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I think it took three months till we were allowed to leave Busserach and join them in [FRENCH].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In [FRENCH] we stayed till August of 1945 when we got certificates.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From Palestine, from the-- actually from the British government, British Mandate Government of Palestine, for legal entry into-- into Palestine.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It took that long.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The war was already over, because they had to find a way to bring us from Switzerland to France to Spain and then charter a ship, a small-- small ship, which brought us to Haifa.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the-- the travel in 1945 was, through Switzerland and France and up to Portbou and then to Barcelona, was by train.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was to Europe, to-- to France just after the-- just after the war, a few months after the liberation actually.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a lot of things were in, of course, still in terrible shape.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we were free.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were under different circumstances.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That is a very interesting story.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In-- in Switzerland, at that time, of course there was no Austrian government that you could require-- I was an Austrian citizen-- that you could get Austrian passports.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The German children couldn't get German passports.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I forgot to mention, we took also in 100 Hungarian children, which came from the Kastner transport.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That is an interesting story, because an American negotiation started with the-- with the Nazi government, Nazi military, to liberate Jews out of the concentration camps in exchange for trucks.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
